series.title: 10-Year Treasury Constant Maturity Rate
series.notes: For further information regarding treasury constant maturity data, please refer to the H.15 Statistical Release notes and to the Treasury Yield Curve Methodology.

series.title: Consumer Price Index for All Urban Consumers: All Items in U.S. City Average
series.notes: The Consumer Price Index for All Urban Consumers: All Items (CPIAUCSL) is a measure of the average change over time in the prices paid by urban consumers for a market basket of consumer goods and services.

series.title: Civilian Unemployment Rate
series.notes: The unemployment rate represents the number of unemployed as a percentage of the labor force.

series.title: Effective Federal Funds Rate
series.notes: Effective federal funds rate is the interest rate at which depository institutions lend reserve balances to other depository institutions overnight, on an uncollateralized basis.

series.title: Gross Domestic Product
series.notes: Gross domestic product (GDP), the featured measure of U.S. output, is the market value of the goods and services produced by labor and property located in the United States.
